### Initialisation
$$
\hat{\mathbf{h}}(0) = \operatorname{zeros}(p)
$$

### Computation
For \( n = 0, 1, 2, \ldots \)

$$
\mathbf{x}(n) = \left[ x(n), x(n-1), \dots, x(n-p+1) \right]^T
$$

$$
e(n) = d(n) - \hat{\mathbf{h}}^H(n)\mathbf{x}(n)
$$

$$
\hat{\mathbf{h}}(n+1) = \hat{\mathbf{h}}(n) + \mu \, e^*(n)\mathbf{x}(n)
$$
